Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a novel formulation of the Signal-to-Interference plus Noise Ratio (SINR) and analyzes the Shannon capacity, which are both related to information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper investigates two new transmission schemes and proposes capacity optimization approaches, which are related to networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking): The paper focuses on satellite communication and proposes new transmission schemes and optimization approaches, which are related to communication and networking. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper develops a general methodology to include technological constraints due to realistic implementations, which is related to systems and control. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper analyzes the performance of the two candidate schemes and identifies the main factors that prevent the two technologies from being dual of each other in practice, which is related to hardware architecture.
